=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_SampleRate_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 441 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: sustained
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 441.2715
  harmonic_decay_rate: -14.8003
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5007
  pitch_clarity: 61.2658
  inharmonicity: 0.0008
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -5.0187
  resonance_freq: 430.6641

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: SampleRate Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/SampleRate.html
// Tags: SampleRate, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
// compares a 441 Hz sine tone derived from sample rate (44100 * 0.01, left)
// with a 440 Hz tone (right), resulting in a 1 Hz beating
(
{
    var freq;
    freq = [SampleRate.ir * 0.01, 440];
    SinOsc.ar(freq, 0, 0.1)
}.play;
)
